2. Here is the kind of chemical rocket that must be built<br>
in leo to send people on a round trip to Mars ,using<br>
chemical propulsion for all required velocity changes.<br>
3. You need 3 kilometers a second in velocity to leave<br>
earth and head for mars. You also need 3 kilometers a<br>
in velocity to decelerate into Mars orbit . Then you need<br>
3 more kilometers a second in velocity to start back to earth.<br>
 Then you need at least 3 more kilometers per second in velocity to decelerate into Earth orbit.Total required<br>
delta V is 12 kilometers a second for this manned mars <br>
mission.<br>
4. The mass of this Rocket after its assembly in leo,<br>
will be 1,500,000 kilograms. All stages will burn H2 + O2<br>
as their chemical fuel. All stages have a specific impulse<br>
of 450 seconds. This is 3,300,000 pounds in leo<br>
5. This will be a three stage rocket. All the stages will have<br>
a mass ratio of 3/1.<br>
6. The cost is about  10,000 U. S.  dollars for each <br>
pound placed in leo to build this rocket.<br>
.7. If H.LV. with 100 ton to leo compacity is available<br>
then about 17 launches is required for orbital launch of<br>
17 construction modules.<br>
8.If only 20 ton to leo M.L.V is available then 85 launches<br>
of 20 ton modules are required. If U. S.  Space shuttle is<br>
 used then 55 launches are required. At 500,000,000 dollars<br>
per flight of the shuttle this will cost 27,500,000,000 dollars<br>
for one such vessel in just leo launch costs.<br>
9.Stage one has 1,200,000  kilograms of fuel stored in<br>
two tanks with a mass of 240,000 kilograms. 20,000 kilograms<br>
of mass is availible for engines.Stage 2 has 160,000 kilograms of fuel stored in two tanks with a mass of 32,000 kilograms.<br>
3000 kilograms is availible for stage two engine.<br>
10. Stage 3 has 30,000 kilograms of fuel stored in two tanks<br>
with a mass of 6,000 kilograms.1000 kilograms is availible <br>
for stage 2 engine. This leaves 8000 kilograms of mass<br>
for the crew module. <br>
11. This is just to orbit mars with a manned mission.<br>
If you intend to land this ship can be scaled up to<br>
a 3,000,000 kilogram mass rocket. This would make<br>
16,000 kilograms of mass availible for Mars landing craft,<br>
and the crew module.This about 35,000 pounds.<br>
If we give it a three person crew then perhaps 8000<br>
kilograms would be availible for The (Mem Mars Excursion Module )<br>
